result.name: Wang Kee Restaurant

reviews.text: Best roast duck I've had in Hong Kong! Very busy during lunch but quite for dinner.

A local in the area recommended this restaurant to me. It is an authentic local restaurant with decent food quality, serving portions, speed and service. The price is comparable to restaurants like it in the area. Neither too strong on spices, sugar, nor salt.  Seating arrangements are slightly crammed, but that is no different to most other restaurants. I would recommend this spot.
Too cramped and a bit dirty. The food is average, but the price is okay. 3 stars.
Waitresses and waiters are nice
